'''Reflections and Debate. On Human Improvement, Visionary Works, and the Cult of the Amateur (1 hour 24 minutes)'''


=Description=

Session from Picnic 2007 in Amsterdam.


- Short introduction by Monique van Dusseldorp, Programme Director PICNIC
- followed by an introduction by moderator Walt Mossberg, Personal Technology Columnist of the Wall Street Journal.
- At 3.45 minutes into the stream, David Weinberger starts his presentation on '[[Everything is Miscellaneous]]'.
- At 47 minutes Weinberger engages in a debate with Andrew Keen, author of The Cult of the Amateur.
